summary: Actor Colin Farrell has launched a foundation in honor of his son, James, who lives with Angelman syndrome, a rare genetic disorder that affects the nervous system. Farrell has opened up about his son's condition, describing him as "extraordinary" and "magic." The foundation aims to raise awareness and support for families affected by Angelman syndrome. Researchers have made progress in developing treatments for the condition, such as ION582, which has been shown to ease symptoms. Parents of children with Angelman syndrome should be aware of the resources available to them, including support groups and organizations like the Angelman Syndrome Foundation.

name: Tim Walz military service
summary: Tim Walz, the Democratic vice presidential nominee, has been the subject of scrutiny regarding his military service. While Walz's decades of experience as an enlisted soldier have been highlighted by his supporters, a former Guardsman has accused him of being a "coward" and "traitor" for retiring before the Iraq war. Other retired National Guardsmen have alleged that Walz "embellished and selectively omitted facts" about his military career. Despite these accusations, Walz has maintained that his service has honed his leadership skills, which he intends to utilize as vice president. Republicans have seized on these allegations to attack Walz's military record, with some suggesting it is akin to the "Swift Boat" smear campaign against John Kerry. Veterans have also expressed dismay, with one Newsweek opinion piece labeling Walz's abandonment of his unit as "unforgivable."

name: Cori Bush primary
summary: In the recent Democratic primary election for Missouri's 1st Congressional District, Wesley Bell emerged victorious, defeating incumbent Cori Bush, a member of the progressive "Squad." Bush faced significant opposition from pro-Israel groups who supported Bell's candidacy. These groups, backed by a super PAC, campaigned heavily against Bush, who previously expressed support for the Boycott, Divestment, and Sanctions (BDS) movement against Israel. The result marks a setback for the progressive wing of the Democratic Party and highlights the influence of pro-Israel groups in shaping election outcomes.

summary: American runner Cole Hocker emerged as an underdog victor in the men's 1,500-meter final at the Paris Olympics, upsetting favored opponents and securing gold. name: Billy Bean
summary: Billy Bean, a prominent figure in baseball known for his groundbreaking role as the second openly gay former MLB player, passed away at the age of 60. Bean's significant contributions to baseball, particularly in the area of diversity and inclusion, are widely acknowledged. After coming out, Bean worked in the league's commissioner's office, playing a crucial role in promoting inclusivity and equality in the sport. His legacy is marked by his unwavering commitment to fostering a diverse and welcoming environment in baseball, earning him widespread recognition and respect throughout the industry.

name: Quincy Hall
summary: In a thrilling turn of events, Quincy Hall of the United States has emerged victorious in the men's 400-meter race at the 2024 Paris Olympics, capturing the gold medal and restoring the title to the United States. Hall's remarkable performance saw him overcome a significant deficit in the final stretch, overtaking three runners to secure the win. His victory marks a significant moment for Team USA, bringing the Olympic 400-meter gold back home after a hiatus. Hall's triumph is particularly noteworthy as he defied the odds, having been underestimated in the lead-up to the Games. His powerful surge to victory has been widely lauded as a testament to his determination and unwavering spirit.
